parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the airbag warning light staying on, deactivating the passenger side airbag, and potentially causing the airbag to deploy spontaneously, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The airbag warning light stays on
the passenger side airbag is deactivated
the airbag light will not turn off
the "passenger airbag off" light will not turn on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake pad wear can lead to reduced stopping power, increased risk of accidents, and costly repairs.
symptoms: and brake pedal feeling tight or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The air intake design flaw can cause water intrusion into the engine, leading to sudden stalling, loss of power, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off suddenly
especially when driving over puddles or in rainy conditions
and may experience water intrusion into the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the serpentine belt can cause a squealing noise, and if left unrepaired, can lead to further damage to the engine and other components.
symptoms: A squealing noise develops on the right side of the engine
and the belt may be glazed or worn out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the check engine light can indicate a potential problem with the engine, which if left unchecked, can lead to further damage or engine failure.
symptoms: The check engine light illuminates while driving
and may be accompanied by other symptoms such as stalling or loss of power.
